  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 20:23-24",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Chronicles 20:23-24",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The children of Ammon and of Moab, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — These fell foul upon the Edomites, and cut them off; and then fell out with one another, and cut one another off. Thus God often makes wicked people instruments of destruction to one another. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "When Judah came toward the watch-tower — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Which stood upon the cliff of Ziz, mentioned ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 20:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and looked toward the wilderness, where their enemies lay encamped, whose numbers, and order, and condition, they could descry from thence. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "They looked unto the multitude, and behold they were dead bodies ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— When they came to the view of this vast army, instead of finding living men to fight with, they found them all dead men, and their carcasses spread as dung upon the face of the earth. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And none escaped ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Or rather, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "none remained, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "because those who were not killed, made the best of their way home; for it cannot be supposed that they were absolutely all killed.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
